== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From {{L.}} [[fundamentum]] "foundation" (from [[fundare]] to lay the bottom, to found) via {{OF.}} fundement and fondement, {{F.}} fondement, and {{OE.}} fundament, fundement, and fondement.
=== Noun ===
# [[foundation]]
# The part of the body upon which one sits; the buttocks; specifically, the [[anus]].
# underlying basis or principle for a theoretical or mathematical system

